WEBVTT

1
00:00:07.180 --> 00:00:10.580
What kept Mr. Roth?
I understood he was coming.

2
00:00:10.660 --> 00:00:14.060
Reeves. what's the protocol?
How long should we stay?

3
00:00:15.420 --> 00:00:20.140
I think a half hour ought to do it. Just
long enough to bring in the New Year.

4
00:00:22.000 --> 00:00:28.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

5
00:00:34.940 --> 00:00:38.140
It's New Year's Eve. Come on.
just for a minute.

6
00:01:49.980 --> 00:01:53.980
There's a plane waiting to take us
to Miami in an hour.

7
00:01:54.140 --> 00:01:56.660
Don't make a big thing about it.

8
00:01:59.900 --> 00:02:03.580
I know it was you. Fredo.
You broke my heart.

9
00:02:05.020 --> 00:02:06.740
You broke my heart!

10
00:02:45.300 --> 00:02:49.660
Due to serious setbacks to our
troops in Guantanamo and Santiago...

11
00:02:50.540 --> 00:02:52.780
...my position in Cuba is untenable.

12
00:02:55.060 --> 00:02:59.060
I am resigning from office
to avoid further bloodshed.

13
00:02:59.740 --> 00:03:02.780
And I shall leave the city immediately.

14
00:03:06.860 --> 00:03:09.740
I wish all of you good luck.

15
00:03:16.820 --> 00:03:19.740
Salud!

16
00:03:20.900 --> 00:03:24.180
Viva la revolución! Viva Fidel!

17
00:03:45.140 --> 00:03:46.620
Fredo!

18
00:03:47.260 --> 00:03:51.060
Come on. Come with me.
It's the only way out of here tonight.

19
00:03:51.620 --> 00:03:53.500
Roth is dead.

20
00:03:54.260 --> 00:03:58.300
Fredo. come with me!
You're still my brother.

21
00:03:59.380 --> 00:04:00.820
Fredo!

22
00:04:24.420 --> 00:04:27.140
I'm Pat Geary. United States Senator.

23
00:04:56.900 --> 00:04:58.780
Fidel! Fidel! Fidel!

24
00:05:37.420 --> 00:05:40.860
Al. Get me a wet towel.

25
00:05:47.060 --> 00:05:49.820
Does Kay know I'm back?

26
00:05:53.740 --> 00:05:56.700
My boy? Did you get him
something for Christmas?

27
00:05:56.780 --> 00:06:00.060
-I took care of it.
-What was it. so I'll know.

28
00:06:00.220 --> 00:06:05.060
It was a little car with an electric motor
that he can ride in. It's nice.

29
00:06:07.460 --> 00:06:09.500
Thank you. Al.

30
00:06:10.540 --> 00:06:13.940
Fellows. could you step outside
for a minute?

31
00:06:30.300 --> 00:06:31.980
Where's my brother?

32
00:06:32.860 --> 00:06:35.940
Roth got out on a private boat.
He's in a hospital in Miami.

33
00:06:36.020 --> 00:06:40.500
He had a stroke. but recovered okay.
Your bodyguard is dead.

34
00:06:40.580 --> 00:06:42.420
I asked about Fredo.

35
00:06:43.380 --> 00:06:46.620
I think he got out.
He must be somewhere in New York.

36
00:06:49.500 --> 00:06:50.860
All right.

37
00:06:52.060 --> 00:06:54.740
I want you to get in touch with him.

38
00:06:54.820 --> 00:06:57.540
I know he's scared.
Tell him everything is all right.

39
00:06:57.660 --> 00:07:02.780
Tell him I know Roth misled him. That
he didn't know they would try to kill me.

40
00:07:03.660 --> 00:07:07.740
-They can come in now.
-There was something else.

41
00:07:08.700 --> 00:07:10.140
What?

42
00:07:16.860 --> 00:07:18.580
What? Come on.

43
00:07:20.540 --> 00:07:22.740
Kay had a miscarriage.

44
00:07:35.140 --> 00:07:37.420
-Was it a boy?
-At three and a half months...

45
00:07:37.500 --> 00:07:40.300
Can't you give me a straight answer?
Was it a boy?

46
00:07:44.260 --> 00:07:46.740
I really don't know.

47
00:08:01.340 --> 00:08:04.220
Poor little Fredo. he's got pneumonia.

48
00:08:47.740 --> 00:08:51.300
Young man. I hear you and
your friends are stealing goods.

49
00:08:51.620 --> 00:08:55.260
But you don't even send a
dress to my house. No respect!

50
00:08:55.820 --> 00:08:57.780
You know I've got three daughters.

51
00:08:58.260 --> 00:08:59.820
This is my neighborhood.

52
00:09:00.660 --> 00:09:03.900
You and your friends should
show me some respect.

53
00:09:04.980 --> 00:09:08.540
You should let me wet
my beak a little.

54
00:09:10.780 --> 00:09:14.300
I hear you and your friends
cleared $600 each.

55
00:09:14.940 --> 00:09:19.260
Give me $200 each. for your own
protection. And I'll forget the insult.

56
00:09:19.620 --> 00:09:24.500
You young punks have to learn
to respect a man like me!

57
00:09:26.700 --> 00:09:29.020
Otherwise the cops will
come to your house.

58
00:09:29.460 --> 00:09:31.900
And your family will be ruined.

59
00:09:33.020 --> 00:09:38.140
Of course if I'm wrong about how much
you stole - I'll take a little less.

60
00:09:38.780 --> 00:09:42.620
And by less. I only mean -
a hundred bucks less.

61
00:09:42.940 --> 00:09:44.700
Now don't refuse me.

62
00:09:46.580 --> 00:09:48.220
Understand. paisan?

63
00:09:54.460 --> 00:09:55.860
I understand.

64
00:09:58.180 --> 00:10:02.660
My friends and I share all the money.
So first. I have to talk to them.

65
00:10:04.020 --> 00:10:08.180
Tell your friends I don't want a lot.
Just enough to wet my beak.

66
00:10:12.220 --> 00:10:14.420
Don't be afraid to tell them!

67
00:10:16.700 --> 00:10:18.420
600 bucks...

68
00:10:18.700 --> 00:10:20.860
Suppose we don't pay?

69
00:10:21.980 --> 00:10:25.300
You know his gang. Tessio.
Real animals.

70
00:10:26.020 --> 00:10:29.300
Maranzalla himself let Fanucci
work this neighborhood.

71
00:10:30.140 --> 00:10:33.500
He's got connections with the cops. too.
We have to pay him.

72
00:10:34.180 --> 00:10:36.060
$200 each...everybody agreed?

73
00:10:40.380 --> 00:10:41.820
Why do we have to pay him?

74
00:10:42.420 --> 00:10:44.620
Vito. leave this to us.

75
00:10:46.140 --> 00:10:48.540
He's one person. we're three.

76
00:10:48.820 --> 00:10:51.380
He's got guns. we've got guns.

77
00:10:51.900 --> 00:10:55.100
Why should we give him the
money we sweated for?

78
00:10:55.340 --> 00:10:57.460
This is his neighborhood!

79
00:10:59.100 --> 00:11:03.420
I know two bookies who don't give
anything to Fanucci.

80
00:11:03.900 --> 00:11:05.380
Who?

81
00:11:05.740 --> 00:11:09.580
Joe The Greek and Frank Pignattaro.

82
00:11:09.660 --> 00:11:11.100
They don't pay Fanucci.

83
00:11:12.820 --> 00:11:17.500
If they don't pay Fanucci. then
somebody else collects for Maranzalla!

84
00:11:18.620 --> 00:11:22.460
We'll all be better off if we
pay him. Don't worry.

85
00:11:37.340 --> 00:11:40.060
Now what I say stays in this room.

86
00:11:40.260 --> 00:11:44.900
If you both like. why not give me
$50 each to pay Fanucci?

87
00:11:47.940 --> 00:11:51.140
I guarantee he'll accept
what I give him.

88
00:11:53.660 --> 00:11:55.900
If Fanucci says $200...

89
00:11:55.980 --> 00:11:57.340
...he means it. Vito!

90
00:11:57.820 --> 00:12:00.660
I'll reason with him.

91
00:12:02.700 --> 00:12:04.620
Leave everything to me.

92
00:12:05.220 --> 00:12:07.220
I'll take care of everything.

93
00:12:08.820 --> 00:12:11.260
I never lie to my friends.

94
00:12:12.060 --> 00:12:14.860
Tomorrow you both go talk to Fanucci.

95
00:12:15.860 --> 00:12:17.620
He'll ask for the money.

96
00:12:18.500 --> 00:12:22.940
Tell him you'll pay whatever
he wants. Don't argue with him.

97
00:12:24.060 --> 00:12:26.620
Then I'll go and get him to agree.

98
00:12:28.740 --> 00:12:31.420
Don't argue with him. since
he's so tough.

99
00:12:32.180 --> 00:12:34.620
How can you get him to take less?

100
00:12:35.340 --> 00:12:37.380
That's my business.

101
00:12:37.700 --> 00:12:40.940
Just remember that I did you a favor.

102
00:12:45.180 --> 00:12:46.700
Is it a deal?

103
00:12:47.740 --> 00:12:48.700
Yes.

104
00:13:34.620 --> 00:13:36.900
His family's out of the house.

105
00:13:37.260 --> 00:13:39.460
Fanucci's alone in the cafe.

106
00:13:44.180 --> 00:13:47.740
Vito. here's my 50 dollars.
Buona fortuna.

107
00:13:58.340 --> 00:14:00.820
Are you sure he's going to go for it?

108
00:14:04.100 --> 00:14:08.220
I'll make an offer he don't refuse.
Don't worry.

109
00:14:39.900 --> 00:14:44.420
It looks like there's -
$100 under my hat.

110
00:14:55.780 --> 00:14:57.900
I was right.

111
00:14:59.260 --> 00:15:00.980
Only $100...

112
00:15:04.220 --> 00:15:06.380
I'm short of money right now.

113
00:15:08.180 --> 00:15:12.580
I've been out of work...so just
give me a little time.

114
00:15:13.420 --> 00:15:15.540
You understand. don't you?

115
00:15:23.420 --> 00:15:25.940
You've got balls. young man!

116
00:15:27.860 --> 00:15:30.780
How come I never heard
of you before?

117
00:15:37.020 --> 00:15:39.340
You've got a lot of guts.

118
00:15:43.140 --> 00:15:45.980
I'll find you some work
for good money.

119
00:15:56.900 --> 00:16:00.980
No hard feelings. right? If I can
help you. let me know.

120
00:16:03.660 --> 00:16:05.980
You've done well for yourself.

121
00:16:09.740 --> 00:16:11.740
Enjoy the festa!

122
00:18:15.740 --> 00:18:17.980
Oh. this is too violent for me!

123
00:20:34.180 --> 00:20:35.580
What've you got there?

124
00:23:07.740 --> 00:23:11.540
Michael. your father loves you
very much.

125
00:26:28.220 --> 00:26:31.700
Mr. Cicci. from the year 1942
to the present time.

126
00:26:31.780 --> 00:26:35.140
you were an employee
of the Genco Olive Oil Company?

127
00:26:35.580 --> 00:26:37.140
That's right.

128
00:26:37.980 --> 00:26:42.020
But in actuality you were a member
of the Corleone crime organization.

129
00:26:44.860 --> 00:26:48.540
No. we called it
the Corleone family. Senator.

130
00:26:48.900 --> 00:26:51.300
What was your position?

131
00:26:52.180 --> 00:26:55.300
At first. like everybody else.
I was a soldier.

132
00:26:55.380 --> 00:26:58.180
-What is that?
-A button. you know. Senator.

133
00:26:58.260 --> 00:27:00.580
No. I don't know. Tell me.

134
00:27:02.060 --> 00:27:07.420
When the boss says "push a button" on
a guy. I push a button. See. Senator?

135
00:27:07.500 --> 00:27:08.820
Mr. Questadt.

136
00:27:09.340 --> 00:27:11.420
-You mean you kill people?
-What?

137
00:27:11.500 --> 00:27:16.420
You kill people at
the behest of your superiors.

138
00:27:20.060 --> 00:27:21.500
Yeah. that's right.

139
00:27:21.580 --> 00:27:26.700
And the head of your family
is Michael Corleone?

140
00:27:26.780 --> 00:27:29.780
Yeah. Counselor. Michael Corleone.

141
00:27:29.860 --> 00:27:33.540
Did you ever get such an order
directly from Michael Corleone?

142
00:27:34.300 --> 00:27:36.300
No. I never talked to him.

143
00:27:36.380 --> 00:27:40.140
Mr. Cicci. could you amplify
your answer a bit?

144
00:27:40.220 --> 00:27:43.420
-Do what?
-Could you expand on your answer?

145
00:27:43.500 --> 00:27:49.060
I'm particularly interested in knowing.
was there always a buffer involved?

146
00:27:49.180 --> 00:27:53.540
Someone in between you
and your superiors who gave the order.

147
00:27:53.620 --> 00:27:57.900
Right. a buffer.
The family had a lot of buffers!

148
00:27:59.700 --> 00:28:03.700
You may find this very amusing. but
the members of this committee do not.

149
00:28:30.780 --> 00:28:32.860
Tell me something. Ma.

150
00:28:36.820 --> 00:28:40.340
What did Papa think...
deep in his heart?

151
00:28:46.660 --> 00:28:48.460
He was being strong...

152
00:28:54.660 --> 00:28:56.220
Strong for his family.

153
00:29:05.620 --> 00:29:08.180
But by being strong for his family...

154
00:29:09.620 --> 00:29:11.380
...could he...

155
00:29:13.220 --> 00:29:14.460
...lose it?

156
00:29:16.340 --> 00:29:21.500
You're thinking about your wife...
about the baby you lost.

157
00:29:23.260 --> 00:29:26.420
But you and your wife can
always have another baby.

158
00:29:28.060 --> 00:29:29.820
No. I meant...lose his family.

159
00:29:33.980 --> 00:29:37.340
But you can never lose your family.

160
00:29:46.460 --> 00:29:48.220
Times are changing.

161
00:30:09.820 --> 00:30:12.180
It's my pleasure.
I don't want money.

162
00:30:12.940 --> 00:30:14.580
Take it as a gift.

163
00:30:17.380 --> 00:30:21.380
If there's something I can do for you.
you come. we talk.

164
00:30:37.340 --> 00:30:40.100
Signora Colombo. why did you
come to see me?

165
00:30:42.940 --> 00:30:46.300
Your wife told me to ask
if you could help me.

166
00:30:48.860 --> 00:30:50.780
She's in bad trouble.

167
00:30:51.420 --> 00:30:55.260
Her neighbors complained to the
landlord about her dog.

168
00:30:56.660 --> 00:30:58.820
He told her to get rid of the animal.

169
00:31:00.380 --> 00:31:04.380
But her little boy loves that dog.
So she hid it.

170
00:31:04.980 --> 00:31:08.620
When the landlord found out. he
got mad and told her to leave.

171
00:31:11.380 --> 00:31:14.100
Now she can't stay even if she
gets rid of it.

172
00:31:14.740 --> 00:31:16.340
I'm so ashamed!

173
00:31:16.700 --> 00:31:20.980
He said he'd get the police to
throw us out on the street.

174
00:31:23.700 --> 00:31:25.220
I'm sorry. but...

175
00:31:27.140 --> 00:31:30.460
I could give you a couple dollars
to help you move.

176
00:31:31.260 --> 00:31:32.660
I can't move!

177
00:31:33.980 --> 00:31:35.820
I want you to talk to him!

178
00:31:36.380 --> 00:31:38.940
Tell him I want to stay here!

179
00:31:46.420 --> 00:31:47.940
What's your landlord's name?

180
00:31:48.380 --> 00:31:50.340
His name is Signor Roberto.

181
00:31:50.900 --> 00:31:53.220
He lives on Fourth Street. near here.

182
00:31:53.820 --> 00:31:56.620
They break the windows.
they dirty the floors...

183
00:31:57.660 --> 00:31:59.140
A real pig-sty. eh?

184
00:32:17.460 --> 00:32:21.260
My name is Vito Corleone.
Signora Colombo is a friend of my wife.

185
00:32:22.140 --> 00:32:25.300
She says she's been evicted
for no good reason.

186
00:32:25.820 --> 00:32:29.900
She's a poor widow. she has nobody
to take care of her.

187
00:32:30.140 --> 00:32:34.020
She has no relatives. no money.
All she has is this neighborhood.

188
00:32:34.380 --> 00:32:37.860
I already rented the place
to another family.

189
00:32:43.180 --> 00:32:47.620
I told her that I'd talk to you.
That you're a reasonable man.

190
00:32:48.820 --> 00:32:52.540
She got rid of the animal that
caused all the trouble.

191
00:32:53.060 --> 00:32:54.900
So let her stay.

192
00:32:54.980 --> 00:32:56.540
Impossible.

193
00:32:57.380 --> 00:32:58.660
Are you Sicilian?

194
00:32:59.060 --> 00:33:00.660
No. I'm Calabrese.

195
00:33:01.300 --> 00:33:04.460
We're practically paisan.
do me this favor.

196
00:33:05.020 --> 00:33:07.580
I already rented it!
I'll look like an idiot.

197
00:33:08.540 --> 00:33:10.740
Besides. the new tenants
pay more rent.

198
00:33:11.260 --> 00:33:13.580
How much more a month?

199
00:33:14.660 --> 00:33:15.700
Five bucks.

200
00:33:20.380 --> 00:33:23.300
Here's six months increase in advance.

201
00:33:24.140 --> 00:33:27.100
But don't tell her about it.
She's very proud.

202
00:33:27.540 --> 00:33:30.020
Come see me in another six months.

203
00:33:31.420 --> 00:33:34.300
Of course. the dog stays. Right?

204
00:33:35.060 --> 00:33:36.140
The dog stays.

205
00:33:40.540 --> 00:33:43.740
Who the hell are you
to come give me orders?

206
00:33:44.100 --> 00:33:47.980
Watch out or I'll kick your Sicilian ass
right into the street!

207
00:33:50.340 --> 00:33:52.020
Do me this favor.

208
00:33:52.860 --> 00:33:54.860
I won't forget it.

209
00:33:55.660 --> 00:33:58.820
Ask your friends in the
neighborhood about me.

210
00:33:59.900 --> 00:34:02.460
They'll tell you I know how
to return a favor.

211
00:34:09.020 --> 00:34:10.860
What a character!

212
00:34:18.460 --> 00:34:23.180
That landlord is here...Roberto.
the one who owns those rat holes.

213
00:34:30.460 --> 00:34:33.660
He's been asking all around
the neighborhood about you.

214
00:34:41.340 --> 00:34:44.020
I hope I'm not disturbing you.
Don Vito.

215
00:34:45.100 --> 00:34:47.260
What can I do for you. Don Roberto?

216
00:34:49.100 --> 00:34:51.060
What a misunderstanding! Holy Mary!

217
00:34:52.340 --> 00:34:55.140
Of course Signora Colombo can stay!

218
00:35:01.100 --> 00:35:03.900
I'm giving back the money you gave me.

219
00:35:05.540 --> 00:35:11.060
Un. due. three. four. five. six. tutt'!

220
00:35:11.900 --> 00:35:16.460
Because after all. Don Vito.
money isn't everything.

221
00:35:24.700 --> 00:35:26.380
Can I sit down?

222
00:35:29.300 --> 00:35:32.180
Your kindness to that widow
made me ashamed of myself.

223
00:35:33.180 --> 00:35:36.060
The rent stays like before!

224
00:35:45.260 --> 00:35:46.660
I'll even lower it.

225
00:35:49.380 --> 00:35:50.620
I'll lower it $5.

226
00:35:54.780 --> 00:35:56.260
I'll lower it $10!

227
00:36:02.460 --> 00:36:04.460
Can I offer you some coffee?

228
00:36:06.740 --> 00:36:11.180
I'm late for an appointment! I can't
this time! Ask me another time!

229
00:36:16.380 --> 00:36:18.740
You'll have to excuse me for now.

230
00:36:23.900 --> 00:36:25.940
I wish I could stay longer!

231
00:36:31.660 --> 00:36:33.980
Just call me and I'll be here!

232
00:36:44.540 --> 00:36:47.260
He won't be back. He'll hide out
in the Bronx!

233
00:37:02.300 --> 00:37:06.940
-Vito. what do you think?
-We'll make a big business!

234
00:37:13.660 --> 00:37:16.700
-New York City.
-Would you speak up. please?

235
00:37:17.380 --> 00:37:18.980
New York City.

236
00:37:19.060 --> 00:37:22.540
-Are you the son of Vito Corleone?
-Yes. I am.

237
00:37:22.620 --> 00:37:26.140
-Where was he born?
-Corleone. Sicily.

238
00:37:26.300 --> 00:37:31.980
Did he at times use an alias that was
known in certain circles as Godfather?

239
00:37:32.740 --> 00:37:38.660
Godfather is a term used by his friends.
One of affection and respect.

240
00:37:39.460 --> 00:37:43.740
Mr. Chairman. I would like to verify
the witness' statement.

241
00:37:43.820 --> 00:37:48.700
For years many of my constituents
have been of Italian descent.

242
00:37:49.020 --> 00:37:51.340
I've come to know them well.

243
00:37:51.460 --> 00:37:55.500
They have honored me
with their support and their friendship.

244
00:37:55.620 --> 00:38:00.620
I can proudly say that some of my
very best friends are Italian-Americans.

245
00:38:01.820 --> 00:38:06.620
However. Mr. Chairman. unfortunately
I have to leave these proceedings

246
00:38:06.780 --> 00:38:10.820
in order to preside over a very important
meeting of my own committee.

247
00:38:11.900 --> 00:38:14.780
Before I leave. I do want to say this.

248
00:38:14.860 --> 00:38:18.980
that these hearings on the Mafia
are in no way whatsoever

249
00:38:19.060 --> 00:38:21.580
a slur upon the great Italian people.

250
00:38:21.660 --> 00:38:24.700
I can state from my own knowledge
and experience

251
00:38:24.780 --> 00:38:29.740
that Italian-Americans are among
the most loyal. most law-abiding.

252
00:38:29.820 --> 00:38:33.180
patriotic. hard-working
American citizens in this land.

253
00:38:34.220 --> 00:38:39.020
It would be a shame. Mr. Chairman.
if we allowed a few rotten apples

254
00:38:39.100 --> 00:38:41.260
to give a bad name to the whole barrel.

255
00:38:41.340 --> 00:38:46.700
Because from the time of Christopher
Columbus to the time of Enrico Fermi

256
00:38:46.780 --> 00:38:48.820
to the present day.

257
00:38:48.980 --> 00:38:53.060
Italian-Americans have been pioneers
in building and defending our nation.

258
00:38:53.500 --> 00:38:58.500
They are the salt of the earth. and
one of the backbones of this country.

259
00:39:04.340 --> 00:39:07.980
I'm sure we all agree
with our esteemed colleague.

260
00:39:08.060 --> 00:39:12.180
Mr. Corleone. you have been advised
as to your legal rights.

261
00:39:12.260 --> 00:39:17.500
We have testimony from
a previous witness. one Willi Cicci.

262
00:39:18.460 --> 00:39:22.700
He stated that you are head of the most
powerful Mafia family in the country.

263
00:39:22.780 --> 00:39:24.980
-Are you?
-No. I'm not.

264
00:39:25.060 --> 00:39:28.220
He testified that you are
personally responsible

265
00:39:28.300 --> 00:39:32.140
for the murder of a New York
police captain in 1947

266
00:39:32.220 --> 00:39:35.660
and with him a man
named Virgil Sollozzo.

267
00:39:35.820 --> 00:39:38.220
-Do you deny this?
-Yes. I do.

268
00:39:38.380 --> 00:39:41.340
Is it true that in the year 1950

269
00:39:41.420 --> 00:39:46.580
you devised the murder of the heads
of "the Five Families" in New York

270
00:39:46.660 --> 00:39:50.100
to assume and consolidate
your nefarious power?

271
00:39:50.180 --> 00:39:53.380
-It's a complete falsehood.
-Mr. Questadt.

272
00:39:53.500 --> 00:39:58.020
Is it true you have a controlling interest
in three major hotels in Las Vegas?

273
00:39:59.100 --> 00:40:04.060
No. it's not true. I own some stock in
some of the hotels there. but very little.

274
00:40:06.580 --> 00:40:10.660
I also have stock in IBM and IT&T.

275
00:40:11.700 --> 00:40:17.700
Do you have any control over gambling
and narcotics in New York State?

276
00:40:17.780 --> 00:40:19.260
No. I do not.

277
00:40:19.340 --> 00:40:22.780
Senator. my client
would like to read a statement.

278
00:40:22.860 --> 00:40:28.220
Mr. Chairman. I think this statement
is totally out of order at this time.

279
00:40:28.380 --> 00:40:33.980
Sir. my client has answered this
committee's questions with sincerity.

280
00:40:34.140 --> 00:40:39.780
He hasn't taken the Fifth Amendment.
so this statement should be heard!

281
00:40:41.660 --> 00:40:46.420
No. I'll allow Mr. Corleone to read
his statement. I'll put it in the record.

282
00:40:48.180 --> 00:40:51.180
In the hopes of clearing
my family name

283
00:40:51.260 --> 00:40:55.060
to give my children their share
of the American way of life

284
00:40:55.140 --> 00:40:58.060
without a blemish on their name
and background.

285
00:40:58.180 --> 00:41:03.180
I have appeared before this committee
and given it all my cooperation.

286
00:41:04.460 --> 00:41:09.780
I consider it a great personal dishonor
to have to deny that I am a criminal.

287
00:41:10.780 --> 00:41:13.980
I wish to have the following noted
for the record...

288
00:41:14.140 --> 00:41:18.020
That I served my country faithfully
in World War Two

289
00:41:18.100 --> 00:41:23.100
and was awarded the Navy Cross
for actions in defense of my country.

290
00:41:23.900 --> 00:41:28.020
That I have never been arrested
or indicted for any crime.

291
00:41:28.180 --> 00:41:31.980
That no proof linking me to any
criminal conspiracy

292
00:41:32.060 --> 00:41:36.740
whether it is called Mafia
or Cosa Nostra or any other name

293
00:41:36.820 --> 00:41:39.060
has ever been made public.

294
00:41:39.220 --> 00:41:41.100
I have not taken refuge
behind the Fifth Amendment.

295
00:41:41.180 --> 00:41:44.220
although it's my right to do so.

296
00:41:46.940 --> 00:41:52.300
I challenge this committee to produce
any witness or evidence against me

297
00:41:52.420 --> 00:41:58.100
and if they do not. I hope they will have
the decency to clear my name

298
00:41:58.180 --> 00:42:01.660
with the same publicity
with which they have besmirched it.

299
00:42:02.980 --> 00:42:08.300
I'm sure we're impressed. Particularly
with your love for our country.

300
00:42:08.460 --> 00:42:11.100
We'll be in recess
until 10:00 a.m. Monday

301
00:42:11.260 --> 00:42:15.820
when we will produce a witness who'll
corroborate the charges against you.

302
00:42:15.980 --> 00:42:20.780
At which time you may very well
be subject to indictment for perjury.

303
00:42:20.860 --> 00:42:25.180
I remind you that you're still
under subpoena. Adjourned!

304
00:42:30.060 --> 00:42:31.700
Ten-to-one shot. you said.

305
00:42:31.780 --> 00:42:36.340
A ten-to-one shot
he would take the Fifth. and I'd lose!

306
00:42:36.420 --> 00:42:40.900
You sound like my bookie.
I owe that monkey my life.

307
00:42:41.900 --> 00:42:45.300
-Well. just get a good night's sleep.
-Yeah.

308
00:42:45.380 --> 00:42:47.460
You've got a big day tomorrow.

309
00:42:47.540 --> 00:42:51.020
I've got you a new suit.
new shirt. new tie.

310
00:42:51.660 --> 00:42:54.820
I'll shave you myself in the morning.

311
00:42:54.980 --> 00:42:58.860
You'll look respectable for 50 million
of your fellow Americans.

312
00:42:58.940 --> 00:43:03.940
Tomorrow... My life won't be worth
a nickel after tomorrow.

313
00:43:04.900 --> 00:43:08.380
Come on! I saw this 19 times.

314
00:43:09.420 --> 00:43:13.060
You've got a great home here.
for the rest of your life.

315
00:43:13.220 --> 00:43:16.220
Nobody gets near you.
you're not going anywhere.

316
00:43:16.380 --> 00:43:21.100
That's great. Beautiful.
Some deal I made.

317
00:43:21.180 --> 00:43:23.900
You'll live like a king. You'll be a hero.

318
00:43:23.980 --> 00:43:26.660
You'll live better here
than most people outside.

319
00:43:26.820 --> 00:43:29.020
Some deal!

320
00:43:31.500 --> 00:43:35.220
Alive. Pentangeli is alive.

321
00:43:36.900 --> 00:43:41.980
-How did they get their hands on him?
-Roth. He engineered it. Michael.

322
00:43:42.820 --> 00:43:45.100
When Frankie went to make a deal with
the Rosato brothers

323
00:43:45.180 --> 00:43:47.140
they tried to kill him.

324
00:43:47.220 --> 00:43:49.380
He thought you double-crossed him.

325
00:43:50.380 --> 00:43:53.580
Our people with the detectives
said he was half dead. scared

326
00:43:53.660 --> 00:43:56.260
and shouted that you'd turned on him.

327
00:43:56.540 --> 00:44:00.540
They already had him on possession.
bookmaking. murder one and more.

328
00:44:02.300 --> 00:44:07.780
The FBI has him airtight.
He's on an army base. 24 hour guards.

329
00:44:07.940 --> 00:44:10.460
We can't get to him. You've opened
yourself to five counts of perjury.

330
00:44:15.020 --> 00:44:17.900
What about Fredo?
What does he know?

331
00:44:17.980 --> 00:44:21.500
He says he doesn't know anything.
and I believe him.

332
00:44:21.660 --> 00:44:25.780
Roth. he played this one beautifully.

333
00:44:32.780 --> 00:44:35.460
I'm going to talk to Fredo.

334
00:45:13.100 --> 00:45:15.700
I haven't got a lot to say. Mike.

335
00:45:17.180 --> 00:45:19.580
We have time.

336
00:45:19.740 --> 00:45:22.780
I was kept pretty much in the dark.

337
00:45:24.060 --> 00:45:26.100
I didn't know all that much.

338
00:45:26.980 --> 00:45:31.620
What about now? Is there anything
you can help me out with?

339
00:45:32.220 --> 00:45:34.340
Anything you can tell me now?

340
00:45:36.220 --> 00:45:38.780
They've got Pentangeli.

341
00:45:52.820 --> 00:45:56.380
I didn't know
it was going to be a hit. Mike.

342
00:45:56.540 --> 00:45:58.740
I swear to God I didn't know.

343
00:46:01.380 --> 00:46:05.540
Johnny Ola bumped into me
in Beverly Hills.

344
00:46:07.300 --> 00:46:10.260
He said that he wanted to talk.

345
00:46:11.740 --> 00:46:17.660
He said that you and Roth
were in on a big deal together.

346
00:46:20.100 --> 00:46:24.260
And that there was something in it
for me if I could help him out.

347
00:46:24.340 --> 00:46:28.100
He said that you were being tough
on the negotiations

348
00:46:28.180 --> 00:46:32.380
but if they could get a little help
and close the deal fast.

349
00:46:33.860 --> 00:46:36.340
it would be good for the family.

350
00:46:37.820 --> 00:46:42.140
And you believed that story?
You believed that?

351
00:46:42.300 --> 00:46:46.220
He said there was something in it
for me. on my own!

352
00:46:46.300 --> 00:46:50.260
-I've always taken care of you. Fredo.
-Taken care of me?

353
00:46:51.540 --> 00:46:54.220
You're my kid brother!
You take care of me?

354
00:46:55.180 --> 00:46:59.100
Did you ever think about that?
Did you ever once think about that?

355
00:47:00.140 --> 00:47:04.140
"Send Fredo off to do this.
send Fredo off to do that!"

356
00:47:04.740 --> 00:47:09.100
"Let Fredo take care of some
Mickey Mouse nightclub somewhere."

357
00:47:09.180 --> 00:47:12.140
"Let Fredo fetch somebody
at the airport!"

358
00:47:12.220 --> 00:47:15.180
I'm your older brother.
but was stepped over!

359
00:47:15.340 --> 00:47:18.940
-It's the way Pop wanted it.
-It's not the way I wanted it!

360
00:47:19.700 --> 00:47:24.380
I can handle things. I'm smart!
Not like everybody says.

361
00:47:24.540 --> 00:47:28.300
Like dumb. I'm smart
and I want respect!

362
00:47:35.660 --> 00:47:40.660
Is there anything you can tell me about
this investigation? Anything more?

363
00:47:48.340 --> 00:47:54.140
The Senate lawyer. Questadt.
He belongs to Roth.

364
00:48:03.420 --> 00:48:05.100
Fredo.

365
00:48:07.460 --> 00:48:09.980
you're nothing to me now.

366
00:48:11.740 --> 00:48:14.100
Not a brother. not a friend.

367
00:48:15.820 --> 00:48:18.700
I don't want to know you.
or what you do.

368
00:48:19.740 --> 00:48:22.620
I don't want to see you at the hotels.

369
00:48:22.700 --> 00:48:25.180
I don't want you near my house.

370
00:48:27.060 --> 00:48:31.540
When you see our mother. I want
to know in advance. so I won't be there.

371
00:48:33.060 --> 00:48:34.620
You understand?

372
00:48:44.020 --> 00:48:45.900
Mikey.

373
00:48:52.220 --> 00:48:55.900
I don't want anything to happen to him
while my mother's alive.

374
00:49:43.740 --> 00:49:47.100
There's more people
than at a ballgame in here.

375
00:49:47.260 --> 00:49:51.260
-Hey. there's Willi Cicci!
-Frankie Five-Angels...

376
00:50:09.860 --> 00:50:12.340
This committee will come to order!

377
00:50:14.980 --> 00:50:17.660
-State your name. please.
-Frank Pentangeli.

378
00:50:17.740 --> 00:50:21.340
-Where were you born?
-Partinico. it's outside of Palermo.

379
00:50:21.500 --> 00:50:23.460
Where do you live now?

380
00:50:23.620 --> 00:50:28.620
I live in an army barracks
with the FBI guys.

381
00:50:29.620 --> 00:50:33.900
We have here a witness
that will further testify

382
00:50:34.020 --> 00:50:40.140
to Michael Corleone's rule of a criminal
empire that controls all gambling.

383
00:50:40.380 --> 00:50:45.100
This witness has had no buffer
between himself and Michael Corleone.

384
00:50:45.180 --> 00:50:48.260
He can corroborate enough charges

385
00:50:48.340 --> 00:50:52.820
for us to recommend a charge
of perjury against Michael Corleone.

386
00:50:52.980 --> 00:50:54.860
-Senator.
-Thank you. Chairman.

387
00:50:56.180 --> 00:50:57.660
Mr. Pentangeli.

388
00:50:58.820 --> 00:51:04.260
Mr. Pentangeli. Were you a member
of the Corleone family?

389
00:51:04.420 --> 00:51:09.260
Did you serve under Caporegime.
Peter Clemenza.

390
00:51:09.340 --> 00:51:13.700
and under Vito Corleone.
also known as the Godfather?

391
00:51:19.180 --> 00:51:21.700
I never knew any Godfather.

392
00:51:24.140 --> 00:51:26.180
I have my own family.

393
00:51:29.460 --> 00:51:31.900
Mr. Pentangeli. you...

394
00:51:32.060 --> 00:51:36.260
You are contradicting
your own sworn statement.

395
00:51:36.380 --> 00:51:39.980
I ask you again. sir.
here and now under oath...

396
00:51:40.060 --> 00:51:44.140
were you at any time a member of
a crime organization

397
00:51:44.220 --> 00:51:46.020
led by Michael Corleone?

398
00:51:46.100 --> 00:51:48.980
I don't know nothing about that!

399
00:51:51.860 --> 00:51:55.660
I was in the olive oil business
with his father

400
00:51:55.740 --> 00:51:58.300
but that was a long time ago.

401
00:51:59.300 --> 00:52:02.260
We have a sworn affidavit.

402
00:52:03.860 --> 00:52:08.380
Your sworn affidavit. that you murdered
on the orders of Michael Corleone.

403
00:52:08.500 --> 00:52:12.820
Do you deny this confession. and do
you realize what will happen if you do?

404
00:52:12.900 --> 00:52:15.940
The FBI guys promised me a deal

405
00:52:16.060 --> 00:52:21.500
so I made up a lot of stuff about
Michael Corleone. just to please them.

406
00:52:21.660 --> 00:52:25.500
But it was all lies. Everything!

407
00:52:26.140 --> 00:52:28.220
They kept saying.

408
00:52:28.300 --> 00:52:33.140
"Michael Corleone did this"
and "Michael Corleone did that".

409
00:52:34.620 --> 00:52:38.460
So I said. "Yeah. sure. Why not?"

410
00:52:38.620 --> 00:52:44.580
Mr. Corleone. would you kindly identify
the gentleman sitting to your left?

411
00:52:44.660 --> 00:52:46.780
I can answer that.

412
00:52:46.940 --> 00:52:49.220
His name is Vincenzo Pentangeli.

413
00:52:50.180 --> 00:52:54.340
-Is he related to the witness?
-He is. I believe. his brother.

414
00:52:54.660 --> 00:52:59.100
-Will he come forward and be sworn?
-He doesn't understand English.

415
00:52:59.260 --> 00:53:02.180
He came at his own expense
to aid his brother.

416
00:53:02.980 --> 00:53:06.540
He's not under subpoena
and has an impeccable reputation.

417
00:53:06.620 --> 00:53:10.260
-He knows nothing about this?
-To my knowledge. nothing.

418
00:53:10.340 --> 00:53:14.420
I'm going to find out what happened!
This committee is now adjourned.

419
00:53:15.100 --> 00:53:17.100
-The witness is excused.
-Senator!

420
00:53:18.140 --> 00:53:21.660
Senator! This committee
owes an apology!

421
00:53:22.140 --> 00:53:25.980
This committee owes an apology.
Apology. Senator!

422
00:53:52.460 --> 00:53:56.300
-Michael. excuse me.
-Hello. darling.

423
00:53:56.700 --> 00:54:00.060
The children are outside. We're going.

424
00:54:01.340 --> 00:54:03.900
What do you mean?
We're leaving tomorrow.

425
00:54:04.700 --> 00:54:07.020
Rocco?

426
00:54:08.020 --> 00:54:10.500
I'll be in my room. Mike.

427
00:54:13.140 --> 00:54:16.100
Michael. I'm not going back to Nevada.

428
00:54:16.180 --> 00:54:19.460
I brought the children
to say goodbye to you.

429
00:54:22.420 --> 00:54:24.860
I'm very happy for you.

430
00:54:25.020 --> 00:54:29.340
I always knew you were too smart
to let any of them beat you.

431
00:54:30.740 --> 00:54:35.140
-Why don't you sit down?
-No. I'm not going to stay long.

432
00:54:35.300 --> 00:54:38.900
There are some things
I'd like to talk to you about.

433
00:54:39.060 --> 00:54:43.900
Things that have been on my mind.
changes I want to make.

434
00:54:44.060 --> 00:54:46.980
I think it's too late for changes. Michael.

435
00:54:48.100 --> 00:54:52.620
-I wasn't going to say anything...
-What do you mean. "too late"?

436
00:54:57.820 --> 00:55:00.380
What really happened with Pentangeli?

437
00:55:05.940 --> 00:55:10.940
-His brother came and helped him.
-I didn't even know he had a brother.

438
00:55:11.100 --> 00:55:12.820
Where is he now?

439
00:55:14.100 --> 00:55:16.660
He's on a plane. back to Sicily.

440
00:55:17.300 --> 00:55:19.740
All he had to do was show his face.

441
00:55:21.340 --> 00:55:25.980
It was between the brothers. Kay.
I had nothing to do with it.

442
00:55:33.500 --> 00:55:37.220
I don't want you going!
Not you. not the kids. No.

443
00:55:38.300 --> 00:55:42.140
You're my wife and my children.
I love you and won't allow it.

444
00:55:43.380 --> 00:55:47.060
You say you love me.
but talk about allowing me to leave!

445
00:55:47.220 --> 00:55:50.780
Things between men and women
will not change.

446
00:55:50.940 --> 00:55:54.660
You've become blind!
Look what's happened to us.

447
00:55:54.820 --> 00:55:59.780
-Look what's happened to our son!
-Nothing's happened to him. He's fine!

448
00:55:59.940 --> 00:56:03.020
-Anthony is not fine!
-I don't want to hear about it.

449
00:56:03.180 --> 00:56:06.940
-Anthony is...
-I don't want to hear about it!

450
00:56:08.220 --> 00:56:10.180
Over!

451
00:56:21.700 --> 00:56:25.180
At this moment
I feel no love for you at all.

452
00:56:26.220 --> 00:56:31.020
I never thought that would ever happen.
but it has.

453
00:56:44.780 --> 00:56:46.780
Kay...

454
00:56:49.500 --> 00:56:51.580
We're leaving tomorrow.

455
00:56:52.260 --> 00:56:55.300
Why don't you take the kids
back to their room?

456
00:56:55.380 --> 00:57:00.980
-Michael. you haven't heard me.
-Kay. what do you want from me?

457
00:57:01.220 --> 00:57:07.340
Do you expect me to let you go.
to let you take my children from me?

458
00:57:08.100 --> 00:57:13.460
Don't you know me? Don't you know
that that's an impossibility?

459
00:57:13.540 --> 00:57:17.300
That I'd use all my power
to keep that from happening?

460
00:57:18.100 --> 00:57:20.380
Don't you know that?

461
00:57:21.980 --> 00:57:23.780
Kay...

462
00:57:26.540 --> 00:57:30.980
In time. you'll feel differently.

463
00:57:32.500 --> 00:57:35.300
You'll be glad I stopped you now.

464
00:57:37.140 --> 00:57:39.060
I know that.

465
00:57:40.980 --> 00:57:44.260
I know you blame me
for losing the baby.

466
00:57:46.020 --> 00:57:47.060
Yes.

467
00:57:48.260 --> 00:57:50.900
I know what that meant to you.

468
00:57:52.860 --> 00:57:54.900
I'll make it up to you. Kay.

469
00:57:55.740 --> 00:57:58.460
I swear I'll make it up to you. I'll...

470
00:57:59.700 --> 00:58:01.540
I'm going to change.

471
00:58:02.940 --> 00:58:06.940
I'll change. I've learned that I have
the strength to change.

472
00:58:09.020 --> 00:58:11.900
Then you'll forget about
this miscarriage

473
00:58:12.700 --> 00:58:17.380
and we'll have another child.
And we'll go on. you and I.

474
00:58:18.660 --> 00:58:22.660
-We'll go on.
-Oh. Michael!

475
00:58:23.740 --> 00:58:26.020
Michael. you are blind.

476
00:58:27.780 --> 00:58:30.020
It wasn't a miscarriage.

477
00:58:31.980 --> 00:58:33.460
It was an abortion.

478
00:58:35.260 --> 00:58:40.220
An abortion. Michael.
Just like our marriage is an abortion.

479
00:58:41.100 --> 00:58:44.420
Something that's unholy and evil!

480
00:58:45.980 --> 00:58:48.220
I didn't want your son. Michael!

481
00:58:49.020 --> 00:58:52.700
I wouldn't bring another one
of your sons into this world!

482
00:58:54.540 --> 00:58:56.940
It was an abortion. Michael.

483
00:58:57.020 --> 00:59:02.460
It was a son and I had it killed
because this must all end!

484
00:59:03.980 --> 00:59:07.900
I know now that it's over. I knew it then.

485
00:59:09.260 --> 00:59:14.020
There would be no way. Michael.
no way you could ever forgive me.

486
00:59:14.460 --> 00:59:18.940
Not with this Sicilian thing
that's been going on for 2.000...

487
00:59:26.540 --> 00:59:29.300
-You won't take my children.
-I will.

488
00:59:29.380 --> 00:59:33.580
-You won't take my children!
-They're my children too.

489
01:00:59.700 --> 01:01:03.100
Fredo. give this to Grandmother.

490
01:03:12.380 --> 01:03:14.300
Don Ciccio. it's Tommasino.

491
01:03:18.060 --> 01:03:20.980
Allow me the honor of
introducing someone.

492
01:03:21.300 --> 01:03:24.020
My partner in America. in New York.

493
01:03:24.660 --> 01:03:26.420
His name is Vito Corleone.

494
01:03:27.100 --> 01:03:29.540
We'll send him olive oil from here.

495
01:03:30.300 --> 01:03:31.700
To his company in America.

496
01:03:36.300 --> 01:03:39.460
They're olive oil importers. Don Ciccio.

497
01:03:48.780 --> 01:03:54.140
We'd like your blessing. and your
permission to start work.

498
01:03:55.220 --> 01:03:57.980
Where is this young man
from New York?

499
01:04:01.180 --> 01:04:04.220
Have him come closer.

500
01:04:05.180 --> 01:04:07.900
I can't see him so good.

501
01:04:14.620 --> 01:04:18.140
My respects. Don Ciccio.
Give me your blessing.

502
01:04:20.540 --> 01:04:22.180
Bless you!

503
01:04:23.980 --> 01:04:25.500
What's your name?

504
01:04:30.700 --> 01:04:33.740
You took the name of this town!

505
01:04:34.260 --> 01:04:35.940
And what's your father's name?

506
01:04:36.060 --> 01:04:39.580
His name was...Antonio Andolini.

507
01:04:39.940 --> 01:04:43.420
Louder. I don't hear so good.

508
01:04:46.740 --> 01:04:49.820
My father's name was
Antonio Andolini...

509
01:04:50.140 --> 01:04:52.740
...and this is for you!

510
01:06:11.300 --> 01:06:13.820
Michael. say goodbye.

511
01:07:14.460 --> 01:07:15.820
Hi. Al.

512
01:07:27.380 --> 01:07:30.260
Can I speak with you
for a second. Tom?

513
01:07:37.860 --> 01:07:39.500
Tom. where's Mike?

514
01:07:40.700 --> 01:07:42.660
Waiting for you to leave.

515
01:07:45.140 --> 01:07:49.500
-Can I talk with him?
-Sorry. Fredo. No chance.

516
01:07:50.060 --> 01:07:53.220
-Can I see him?
-He's in the boathouse.

517
01:08:05.780 --> 01:08:08.060
Michael. it's Connie.

518
01:08:28.460 --> 01:08:29.980
Michael...

519
01:08:32.860 --> 01:08:36.220
I'd like to stay close to home now.
if it's all right.

520
01:08:44.380 --> 01:08:46.540
Is Kay coming?

521
01:08:48.900 --> 01:08:50.500
No.

522
01:08:58.300 --> 01:09:01.020
Fredo's in the house with Mama.

523
01:09:01.100 --> 01:09:04.860
He asked for you
and Tom said you wouldn't see him.

524
01:09:08.380 --> 01:09:10.140
That's right.

525
01:09:12.860 --> 01:09:16.100
Kids. why don't you go outside
for a while?

526
01:09:19.540 --> 01:09:21.820
Please. I want to talk to you.

527
01:09:32.860 --> 01:09:36.700
Michael. I hated you for so many years.

528
01:09:37.140 --> 01:09:42.260
I think I did things to myself.
to hurt myself. so that you'd know

529
01:09:45.340 --> 01:09:47.380
that I could hurt you.

530
01:09:53.220 --> 01:09:57.460
You were just being strong for all of us.
the way Papa was.

531
01:09:58.020 --> 01:09:59.820
And I forgive you.

532
01:10:04.300 --> 01:10:06.180
Can't you forgive Fredo?

533
01:10:07.180 --> 01:10:11.620
He's so sweet.
and helpless without you.

534
01:10:17.700 --> 01:10:21.380
You need me.
I want to take care of you now.

535
01:10:30.820 --> 01:10:32.300
Connie.

536
01:12:10.340 --> 01:12:12.860
Tom. sit down.

537
01:12:24.100 --> 01:12:27.700
Our friend and business partner.
Hyman Roth. is in the news.

538
01:12:29.020 --> 01:12:33.460
-Did you hear about it?
-I hear that he's in Israel.

539
01:12:33.980 --> 01:12:38.420
The High Court in Israel
turned down his request to live there.

540
01:12:38.580 --> 01:12:42.020
His passport's been invalidated.
except to return here.

541
01:12:42.100 --> 01:12:44.740
He landed in Buenos Aires yesterday.

542
01:12:45.020 --> 01:12:48.780
He offered them a million dollars
if they'd let him live there.

543
01:12:49.700 --> 01:12:53.540
-They turned him down.
-He's going to try Panama.

544
01:12:53.660 --> 01:12:58.140
Panama won't take him.
Not for a million. not for ten million.

545
01:12:58.500 --> 01:13:03.020
His condition is reported as terminal.
He's only got six months left.

546
01:13:03.180 --> 01:13:06.060
He's had the same heart attack
for 20 years.

547
01:13:06.220 --> 01:13:10.220
-That plane goes to Miami.
-That's right. That's where I want it met.

548
01:13:11.300 --> 01:13:16.460
Impossible. They'll turn him over to the
Internal Revenue. Customs and FBI.

549
01:13:16.620 --> 01:13:19.700
It's not impossible.
Nothing's impossible.

550
01:13:19.780 --> 01:13:21.180
It would be
like trying to kill the President.

551
01:13:21.260 --> 01:13:25.580
-There's no way we can get to him!
-Tom. you surprise me.

552
01:13:28.260 --> 01:13:31.740
If anything in this life is certain.

553
01:13:31.820 --> 01:13:34.900
if history has taught us anything.

554
01:13:34.980 --> 01:13:37.500
it's that you can kill anyone.

555
01:13:42.620 --> 01:13:47.340
-Rocco?
-Difficult. Not impossible.

556
01:13:47.660 --> 01:13:49.300
Good.

557
01:13:51.660 --> 01:13:55.100
Why did you ask me if something
was wrong when I came in?

558
01:13:58.620 --> 01:14:04.300
I thought you were going to tell me that
you were moving your family to Vegas

559
01:14:05.620 --> 01:14:09.340
and that you'd been offered the Vice
Presidency of the Houstan hotels there.

560
01:14:11.380 --> 01:14:16.020
-I thought you'd tell me that.
-Must I tell you every offer I turn down?

561
01:14:20.060 --> 01:14:22.740
-Let's do business.
-All right.

562
01:14:24.540 --> 01:14:27.420
Just consider this. Michael.
Just consider it.

563
01:14:28.620 --> 01:14:30.660
Roth and the Rosatos are on the run.

564
01:14:30.740 --> 01:14:33.180
Are they worth it.
are they strong enough?

565
01:14:33.660 --> 01:14:38.340
Is it worth it? You've won.
Do you want to wipe everybody out?

566
01:14:38.420 --> 01:14:43.540
I don't feel I have to wipe everybody
out. Tom. Just my enemies. that's all.

567
01:14:50.940 --> 01:14:53.500
Are you with me in these things.
or what?

568
01:14:55.540 --> 01:15:00.740
Because if not. you can take your wife.
your family and your mistress

569
01:15:00.900 --> 01:15:03.900
and move them all to Las Vegas.

570
01:15:06.900 --> 01:15:11.740
Why do you hurt me. Michael? I've
always been loyal to you. What is this?

571
01:15:16.140 --> 01:15:17.740
So...you're staying?

572
01:15:19.700 --> 01:15:21.940
Yes. I'm staying.

573
01:15:24.420 --> 01:15:26.460
What do you want me to do?

574
01:15:26.940 --> 01:15:28.860
Hey. Anthony.

575
01:15:29.380 --> 01:15:33.820
How would you like it if I taught you
how to catch the really big fish?

576
01:15:33.900 --> 01:15:36.300
-Would you like that?
-Okay.

577
01:15:36.460 --> 01:15:38.980
You know. when I was your age.

578
01:15:39.420 --> 01:15:46.020
I went out fishing with all my brothers
and my father. Everybody.

579
01:15:47.140 --> 01:15:50.500
I was the only one that caught a fish.

580
01:15:52.420 --> 01:15:55.340
Nobody else could catch one.
Do you know how I did it?

581
01:15:56.860 --> 01:16:00.500
Every time I put the line in the water
I said a Hail Mary

582
01:16:00.660 --> 01:16:04.140
and every time I said a Hail Mary.
I caught a fish.

583
01:16:06.460 --> 01:16:10.460
Do you believe that? It's true.
That's the secret.

584
01:16:12.460 --> 01:16:16.140
-Do you want to try it out on the lake?
-Okay.

585
01:16:17.860 --> 01:16:19.140
What else have you got?

586
01:16:44.620 --> 01:16:47.100
Everything will be okay.

587
01:16:47.260 --> 01:16:51.020
-Did my brother go back?
-Yeah. don't worry.

588
01:16:51.180 --> 01:16:55.900
He's ten times tougher than me.
my brother. He's old-fashioned.

589
01:16:56.900 --> 01:17:00.060
He didn't want dinner.
just wanted to go home.

590
01:17:00.140 --> 01:17:04.980
That's my brother! Nothing could get
him away from that two-mule town.

591
01:17:05.140 --> 01:17:08.820
He could have been big here.
He could have had his own family.

592
01:17:13.820 --> 01:17:15.700
Tom.

593
01:17:16.380 --> 01:17:18.860
what do I do now?

594
01:17:19.540 --> 01:17:21.460
Frankie.

595
01:17:25.820 --> 01:17:29.660
You were always interested
in politics and history.

596
01:17:31.100 --> 01:17:34.420
I remember you talking about Hitler
back in '33.

597
01:17:34.580 --> 01:17:38.060
Yeah. I still read a lot.
I get good stuff in there.

598
01:17:40.500 --> 01:17:46.020
You were around the old-timers. who
built the organization of the families.

599
01:17:46.140 --> 01:17:51.340
basing them on the old Roman legions.
with "regimes." "capos" and "soldiers".

600
01:17:52.540 --> 01:17:56.380
-And it worked.
-Yeah. it worked.

601
01:17:57.140 --> 01:18:00.500
Those were the great old days.
you know.

602
01:18:00.660 --> 01:18:03.660
We was like the Roman Empire.

603
01:18:03.740 --> 01:18:07.100
The Corleone family
was like the Roman Empire.

604
01:18:09.380 --> 01:18:11.260
Yeah.

605
01:18:11.420 --> 01:18:13.700
it was once.

606
01:18:17.940 --> 01:18:19.420
Frankie.

607
01:18:29.460 --> 01:18:32.860
When a plot
against the Emperor failed

608
01:18:34.060 --> 01:18:37.380
the plotters were always
given a chance

609
01:18:39.260 --> 01:18:42.700
to let their families keep their fortunes.
Right?

610
01:18:42.780 --> 01:18:44.820
Only the rich guys.

611
01:18:44.900 --> 01:18:49.700
The little guys got knocked off and all
their estates went to the Emperors.

612
01:18:49.860 --> 01:18:54.860
Unless they went home and killed
themselves. then nothing happened.

613
01:18:55.980 --> 01:19:00.100
And their families were taken care of.

614
01:19:01.660 --> 01:19:04.900
That was a good break. a nice deal.

615
01:19:05.500 --> 01:19:06.940
Yeah.

616
01:19:07.820 --> 01:19:09.820
They went home

617
01:19:10.980 --> 01:19:13.820
and sat in a hot bath

618
01:19:13.980 --> 01:19:16.420
opened up their veins

619
01:19:16.580 --> 01:19:19.180
and bled to death.

620
01:19:20.300 --> 01:19:24.300
And sometimes they had a little party
before they did it.

621
01:19:29.420 --> 01:19:31.660
Don't worry about anything.
Frankie Five-Angels.

622
01:19:33.060 --> 01:19:36.220
Thanks. Tom. Thanks.

623
01:19:53.940 --> 01:19:56.940
-See you. Tom.
-Addio. Frankie.

624
01:20:07.420 --> 01:20:10.420
Kay. You have to go.

625
01:20:12.140 --> 01:20:15.340
-So pretty...
-Kay. please hurry. He's coming.

626
01:20:23.780 --> 01:20:27.420
Anthony. Kiss Mama goodbye.

627
01:20:29.940 --> 01:20:32.620
Anthony. kiss your mother goodbye!

628
01:20:32.780 --> 01:20:37.660
Anthony. say goodbye to Mama.
Anthony. I love you. Anthony.

629
01:20:38.740 --> 01:20:41.060
Kay. please.

630
01:20:43.820 --> 01:20:45.700
All right.

631
01:20:58.420 --> 01:21:00.700
Mary. come here.

632
01:21:07.580 --> 01:21:09.100
Anthony.

633
01:21:09.180 --> 01:21:12.060
Anthony. please. Kiss me once.

634
01:22:47.100 --> 01:22:49.140
Easy.

635
01:22:54.580 --> 01:22:57.540
Anthony! Anthony!

636
01:22:57.660 --> 01:23:00.580
-He's here. we're going fishing.
-No!

637
01:23:00.740 --> 01:23:03.940
Michael wants to take him to Reno now.

638
01:23:04.020 --> 01:23:05.940
Shit!

639
01:23:07.100 --> 01:23:10.420
Okay. kid. you have to go to Reno
with your pop.

640
01:23:11.340 --> 01:23:15.140
-I'll take you fishing tomorrow. okay?
-Okay.

641
01:23:18.620 --> 01:23:20.140
Hey. Anthony.

642
01:23:20.220 --> 01:23:24.380
Listen. I'll catch one for you in secret.

643
01:23:28.260 --> 01:23:29.580
Let's go.

644
01:24:07.140 --> 01:24:11.140
-Mr. Roth. I must take you into custody.
-I understand.

645
01:24:11.300 --> 01:24:14.300
What's your reaction
to the Israeli High Court ruling?

646
01:24:14.460 --> 01:24:17.140
I'm a retired investor on a pension.

647
01:24:17.300 --> 01:24:21.980
I went to Israel to live there as a Jew.
in the twilight of my life.

648
01:24:28.060 --> 01:24:31.540
Hey. Frankie! Come on out.
let's play some Hearts.

649
01:24:39.380 --> 01:24:41.020
Frankie!

650
01:24:56.260 --> 01:24:59.020
Is it true you're worth
over 300 million dollars?

651
01:24:59.180 --> 01:25:02.660
I'm a retired investor.
living on a pension.

652
01:25:02.820 --> 01:25:06.220
I came home to vote
in the presidential election

653
01:25:06.380 --> 01:25:09.660
because they wouldn't give me
an absentee ballot.

654
01:25:21.500 --> 01:25:23.820
Jesus Christ.

655
01:25:24.820 --> 01:25:29.260
Hail Mary. full of grace.
The Lord is with thee.

656
01:25:30.700 --> 01:25:33.180
Blessed art thou amongst women.

657
01:25:33.940 --> 01:25:36.940
Blessed is the fruit of thy womb. Jesus.

658
01:25:38.100 --> 01:25:42.140
Holy Mary. Mother of God.
pray for us sinners.

659
01:26:22.300 --> 01:26:27.260
Hey! Everybody. pay attention.
This is my friend Carlo Rizzi.

660
01:26:28.060 --> 01:26:30.660
-You know my brother Fredo.
-Sure.

661
01:26:30.820 --> 01:26:35.380
This is my stepbrother Tom.
and that's his girl Theresa.

662
01:26:35.460 --> 01:26:38.660
This cute little thing is my sister Connie.

663
01:26:38.740 --> 01:26:41.460
Say hello to Carlo.
He's good-looking. isn't he?

664
01:26:41.540 --> 01:26:43.060
Yes.

665
01:26:43.220 --> 01:26:47.100
The droopy thing is Mike.
We call him Joe College.

666
01:26:47.580 --> 01:26:51.300
Sit down. Talk to each other.

667
01:26:51.460 --> 01:26:53.620
Hey. Mr. Einstein...

668
01:26:56.820 --> 01:26:59.220
-The cake.
-Sally. get in here!

669
01:26:59.380 --> 01:27:01.420
-I was scared.
-Come on.

670
01:27:02.060 --> 01:27:05.260
-Where's your father?
-Christmas shopping.

671
01:27:05.420 --> 01:27:07.700
Let's see that thing.

672
01:27:09.340 --> 01:27:11.180
That's nice!

673
01:27:11.260 --> 01:27:14.940
-Should I put the candles on now?
-Yeah. You help her. Carlo.

674
01:27:16.020 --> 01:27:19.020
-What is that? Rum?
-Yeah.

675
01:27:23.820 --> 01:27:26.940
Don't touch the antipasto
until Pop sees it.

676
01:27:27.100 --> 01:27:29.660
He's not ugly...

677
01:27:34.940 --> 01:27:40.940
What do you think of the nerve of those
Japs? Bombing us on Pop's birthday.

678
01:27:41.020 --> 01:27:44.300
They didn't know it was Pop's birthday.

679
01:27:44.380 --> 01:27:46.940
Not surprising after the oil embargo.

680
01:27:47.100 --> 01:27:51.420
They've got no right dropping bombs!
Are you a Jap-lover?

681
01:27:51.580 --> 01:27:55.100
-30.000 enlisted this morning.
-Bunch of saps...

682
01:27:55.260 --> 01:27:58.620
-Why are they saps?
-Let's not talk about the war.

683
01:27:59.700 --> 01:28:01.460
You talk to Carlo.

684
01:28:03.340 --> 01:28:06.780
Only saps risk their lives for strangers.

685
01:28:06.860 --> 01:28:10.180
-That's Pop talking.
-You're right. that's Pop talking!

686
01:28:10.300 --> 01:28:13.940
-They risk their lives for their country.
-Country isn't your blood.

687
01:28:14.020 --> 01:28:19.700
-I don't feel that way.
-Then quit college and join the army!

688
01:28:19.780 --> 01:28:21.220
I did.

689
01:28:22.140 --> 01:28:24.980
I've enlisted in the Marines.

690
01:28:27.100 --> 01:28:30.220
-Why didn't you come to us?
-What do you mean?

691
01:28:30.300 --> 01:28:34.380
-Pop managed to get you a deferment.
-I didn't ask for it.

692
01:28:35.100 --> 01:28:37.100
I didn't want it.

693
01:28:38.220 --> 01:28:40.540
Come on! Knock it off!

694
01:28:40.700 --> 01:28:44.300
-Punk!
-Sonny. sit down.

695
01:28:47.180 --> 01:28:50.540
Mommy. Daddy's fighting again!

696
01:28:53.500 --> 01:28:56.140
Go and show Carlo the tree.

697
01:29:06.020 --> 01:29:10.820
Nice.

698
01:29:11.420 --> 01:29:13.980
Break your father's heart
on his birthday.

699
01:29:15.060 --> 01:29:17.700
That's swell. Mike. Congratulations.

700
01:29:17.780 --> 01:29:19.820
Don't encourage him!

701
01:29:19.900 --> 01:29:22.500
Get me a drink. Go on!

702
01:29:26.180 --> 01:29:29.500
You don't understand.
Your father has plans for you.

703
01:29:29.660 --> 01:29:33.700
Many times he and I have talked
about your future.

704
01:29:35.420 --> 01:29:39.100
You've talked to my father
about my future?

705
01:29:40.340 --> 01:29:44.460
-My future.
-Mikey. he has high hopes for you.

706
01:29:44.540 --> 01:29:49.860
-I have my own plans for my future.
-Did you go to college to get stupid?

707
01:29:49.940 --> 01:29:51.780
He's here!

708
01:29:53.620 --> 01:29:55.500
Come on.

709
01:29:57.660 --> 01:29:59.540
Stupid!

710
01:30:16.100 --> 01:30:18.380
Surprise!

711
01:30:21.340 --> 01:30:26.780
For he's a jolly good fellow
For he's a jolly good fellow

712
01:30:26.980 --> 01:30:30.620
That nobody can deny
Nobody can deny...

713
01:30:31.305 --> 01:31:31.595
